---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of use — PDF Tools" description="The rules for using pdf.oriz.in." hideSidebar={true}>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">PDF Tools</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Terms</p>
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      By using pdf.oriz.in or any <code>*.oriz.in</code> site, you agree to these terms.
      They are short on purpose.
    </p>

    <h2>Use the sites lawfully</h2>
    <p>
      Don't try to break the sites, scrape them at abusive rates, or use them
      to harass others. Account takeover, copyright infringement, and any
      activity prohibited under Indian law are forbidden.
    </p>

    <h2>Tools are provided as-is</h2>
    <p>
      The PDF tools on pdf.oriz.in are provided for information and convenience
      only. They are not professional advice or a substitute for any specific
      regulated process (e.g. legally-binding e-signatures often require a
      qualified provider). Verify outputs before relying on them.
      See the full <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">disclaimer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      Your PDFs never reach our servers — every tool runs in your browser. Anything
      you save through your account (preferences, recently-used tools) stays yours.
      You grant us a limited licence to store and serve that content back to you.
    </p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can delete your account at any time from the
      <a href="/account/">account page</a>. We can suspend accounts engaged in
      abuse without notice.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, pdf.oriz.in and its operator are
      not liable for any indirect or consequential damages arising from use of
      the tools.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of India. Disputes will be settled
      in the courts of Bhubaneswar, Odisha.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { max-width: var(--container-prose, 720px); margin-inline: auto; padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif, Georgia, serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .meta { color: var(--color-fg-soft); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
  .prose { max-width: var(--container-prose, 720px); margin-inline: auto; padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif, Georgia, serif); font-size: 1.375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .prose code { background: var(--color-bg-muted); padding: 0.125em 0.375em; border-radius: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.875em; }
</style>
